parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or stop running, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Oil leaks can cause damage to other engine components, leading to costly repairs.
Electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to stall or stop running, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause a fire hazard, leading to injuries or fatalities.
ABS and ESC system failure can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or loss of control.
Instrument console failure can cause the vehicle's warning systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries.
Throttle control device failure can cause the vehicle to slow down or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
RPM meter failure can cause the vehicle's performance to be affected, leading to accidents or injuries.
Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
